{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I know what you're thinking."},{"time":3000,"text":"You think I've lost my way,"},{"time":5000,"text":"and somebody's going to come on the stage in a minute"},{"time":7000,"text":"and guide me gently back to my seat."},{"time":9000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":15000,"text":"I get that all the time in Dubai."},{"time":18000,"text":"\"Here on holiday are you, dear?\""},{"time":20000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":22000,"text":"\"Come to visit the children?"},{"time":25000,"text":"How long are you staying?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":27000,"text":"Well actually, I hope for a while longer yet."},{"time":30000,"text":"I have been living and teaching in the Gulf"},{"time":33000,"text":"for over 30 years."},{"time":35000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":39000,"text":"And in that time, I have seen a lot of changes."},{"time":43000,"text":"Now that statistic"},{"time":45000,"text":"is quite shocking."},{"time":47000,"text":"And I want to talk to you today"},{"time":49000,"text":"about language loss"},{"time":51000,"text":"and the globalization of English."},{"time":54000,"text":"I want to tell you about my friend"},{"time":56000,"text":"who was teaching English to adults in Abu Dhabi."},{"time":59000,"text":"And one fine day,"},{"time":61000,"text":"she decided to take them into the garden"},{"time":63000,"text":"to teach them some nature vocabulary."},{"time":65000,"text":"But it was she who ended up learning"},{"time":67000,"text":"all the Arabic words for the local plants,"},{"time":69000,"text":"as well as their uses --"},{"time":71000,"text":"medicinal uses, cosmetics,"},{"time":74000,"text":"cooking, herbal."},{"time":77000,"text":"How did those students get all that knowledge?"},{"time":79000,"text":"Of course, from their grandparents"},{"time":81000,"text":"and even their great-grandparents."},{"time":84000,"text":"It's not necessary to tell you how important it is"},{"time":87000,"text":"to be able to communicate"},{"time":89000,"text":"across generations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91000,"text":"But sadly, today,"},{"time":93000,"text":"languages are dying"},{"time":95000,"text":"at an unprecedented rate."},{"time":97000,"text":"A language dies every 14 days."},{"time":101000,"text":"Now, at the same time,"},{"time":103000,"text":"English is the undisputed global language."},{"time":105000,"text":"Could there be a connection?"},{"time":107000,"text":"Well I don't know."},{"time":109000,"text":"But I do know that I've seen a lot of changes."},{"time":112000,"text":"When I first came out to the Gulf, I came to Kuwait"},{"time":115000,"text":"in the days when it was still a hardship post."},{"time":118000,"text":"Actually, not that long ago."},{"time":120000,"text":"That is a little bit too early."},{"time":123000,"text":"But nevertheless,"},{"time":125000,"text":"I was recruited by the British Council,"},{"time":127000,"text":"along with about 25 other teachers."},{"time":129000,"text":"And we were the first non-Muslims"},{"time":131000,"text":"to teach in the state schools there in Kuwait."},{"time":134000,"text":"We were brought to teach English"},{"time":136000,"text":"because the government wanted to modernize the country"},{"time":140000,"text":"and to empower the citizens through education."},{"time":143000,"text":"And of course, the U.K. benefited"},{"time":145000,"text":"from some of that lovely oil wealth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":148000,"text":"Okay."},{"time":150000,"text":"Now this is the major change that I've seen --"},{"time":153000,"text":"how teaching English"},{"time":155000,"text":"has morphed"},{"time":157000,"text":"from being a mutually beneficial practice"},{"time":161000,"text":"to becoming a massive international business that it is today."},{"time":164000,"text":"No longer just a foreign language on the school curriculum,"},{"time":168000,"text":"and no longer the sole domain"},{"time":170000,"text":"of mother England,"},{"time":172000,"text":"it has become a bandwagon"},{"time":174000,"text":"for every English-speaking nation on earth."},{"time":177000,"text":"And why not?"},{"time":179000,"text":"After all, the best education --"},{"time":182000,"text":"according to the latest World University Rankings --"},{"time":185000,"text":"is to be found in the universities"},{"time":187000,"text":"of the U.K. and the U.S."},{"time":191000,"text":"So everybody wants to have an English education, naturally."},{"time":195000,"text":"But if you're not a native speaker,"},{"time":197000,"text":"you have to pass a test."}]},{"cues":[{"time":199000,"text":"Now can it be right"},{"time":201000,"text":"to reject a student"},{"time":203000,"text":"on linguistic ability alone?"},{"time":205000,"text":"Perhaps you have a computer scientist"},{"time":207000,"text":"who's a genius."},{"time":209000,"text":"Would he need the same language as a lawyer, for example?"},{"time":212000,"text":"Well, I don't think so."},{"time":216000,"text":"We English teachers reject them all the time."},{"time":219000,"text":"We put a stop sign,"},{"time":221000,"text":"and we stop them in their tracks."},{"time":223000,"text":"They can't pursue their dream any longer,"},{"time":225000,"text":"'til they get English."},{"time":229000,"text":"Now let me put it this way:"},{"time":232000,"text":"if I met a monolingual Dutch speaker"},{"time":236000,"text":"who had the cure for cancer,"},{"time":238000,"text":"would I stop him from entering my British University?"},{"time":241000,"text":"I don't think so."},{"time":243000,"text":"But indeed, that is exactly what we do."},{"time":246000,"text":"We English teachers are the gatekeepers."},{"time":249000,"text":"And you have to satisfy us first"},{"time":252000,"text":"that your English is good enough."},{"time":256000,"text":"Now it can be dangerous"},{"time":258000,"text":"to give too much power"},{"time":261000,"text":"to a narrow segment of society."},{"time":263000,"text":"Maybe the barrier would be too universal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266000,"text":"Okay."},{"time":268000,"text":"\"But,\" I hear you say,"},{"time":271000,"text":"\"what about the research?"},{"time":273000,"text":"It's all in English.\""},{"time":275000,"text":"So the books are in English,"},{"time":277000,"text":"the journals are done in English,"},{"time":279000,"text":"but that is a self-fulfilling prophecy."},{"time":282000,"text":"It feeds the English requirement."},{"time":284000,"text":"And so it goes on."},{"time":286000,"text":"I ask you, what happened to translation?"},{"time":289000,"text":"If you think about the Islamic Golden Age,"},{"time":293000,"text":"there was lots of translation then."},{"time":296000,"text":"They translated from Latin and Greek"},{"time":299000,"text":"into Arabic, into Persian,"},{"time":301000,"text":"and then it was translated on"},{"time":303000,"text":"into the Germanic languages of Europe"},{"time":305000,"text":"and the Romance languages."},{"time":307000,"text":"And so light shone upon the Dark Ages of Europe."},{"time":312000,"text":"Now don't get me wrong;"},{"time":314000,"text":"I am not against teaching English,"},{"time":316000,"text":"all you English teachers out there."},{"time":318000,"text":"I love it that we have a global language."},{"time":320000,"text":"We need one today more than ever."},{"time":323000,"text":"But I am against using it"},{"time":325000,"text":"as a barrier."},{"time":327000,"text":"Do we really want to end up with 600 languages"},{"time":330000,"text":"and the main one being English, or Chinese?"},{"time":333000,"text":"We need more than that. Where do we draw the line?"},{"time":336000,"text":"This system"},{"time":338000,"text":"equates intelligence"},{"time":341000,"text":"with a knowledge of English,"},{"time":344000,"text":"which is quite arbitrary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":346000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":352000,"text":"And I want to remind you"},{"time":354000,"text":"that the giants upon whose shoulders"},{"time":357000,"text":"today's intelligentsia stand"},{"time":359000,"text":"did not have to have English,"},{"time":361000,"text":"they didn't have to pass an English test."},{"time":363000,"text":"Case in point, Einstein."},{"time":367000,"text":"He, by the way, was considered remedial at school"},{"time":370000,"text":"because he was, in fact, dyslexic."},{"time":372000,"text":"But fortunately for the world,"},{"time":374000,"text":"he did not have to pass an English test."},{"time":377000,"text":"Because they didn't start until 1964"},{"time":380000,"text":"with TOEFL,"},{"time":382000,"text":"the American test of English."},{"time":384000,"text":"Now it's exploded."},{"time":386000,"text":"There are lots and lots of tests of English."},{"time":389000,"text":"And millions and millions of students"},{"time":391000,"text":"take these tests every year."},{"time":393000,"text":"Now you might think, you and me,"},{"time":395000,"text":"\"Those fees aren't bad, they're okay,\""},{"time":397000,"text":"but they are prohibitive"},{"time":399000,"text":"to so many millions of poor people."},{"time":401000,"text":"So immediately, we're rejecting them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":403000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":406000,"text":"It brings to mind a headline I saw recently:"},{"time":409000,"text":"\"Education: The Great Divide.\""},{"time":411000,"text":"Now I get it,"},{"time":413000,"text":"I understand why people would want to focus on English."},{"time":416000,"text":"They want to give their children the best chance in life."},{"time":420000,"text":"And to do that, they need a Western education."},{"time":423000,"text":"Because, of course, the best jobs"},{"time":425000,"text":"go to people out of the Western Universities,"},{"time":428000,"text":"that I put on earlier."},{"time":430000,"text":"It's a circular thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":432000,"text":"Okay."},{"time":434000,"text":"Let me tell you a story about two scientists,"},{"time":436000,"text":"two English scientists."},{"time":438000,"text":"They were doing an experiment"},{"time":440000,"text":"to do with genetics"},{"time":442000,"text":"and the forelimbs and the hind limbs of animals."},{"time":445000,"text":"But they couldn't get the results they wanted."},{"time":447000,"text":"They really didn't know what to do,"},{"time":449000,"text":"until along came a German scientist"},{"time":452000,"text":"who realized that they were using two words"},{"time":455000,"text":"for forelimb and hind limb,"},{"time":457000,"text":"whereas genetics does not differentiate"},{"time":461000,"text":"and neither does German."},{"time":463000,"text":"So bingo,"},{"time":465000,"text":"problem solved."},{"time":467000,"text":"If you can't think a thought,"},{"time":469000,"text":"you are stuck."},{"time":472000,"text":"But if another language can think that thought,"},{"time":474000,"text":"then, by cooperating,"},{"time":476000,"text":"we can achieve and learn so much more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":481000,"text":"My daughter"},{"time":483000,"text":"came to England from Kuwait."},{"time":486000,"text":"She had studied science and mathematics in Arabic."},{"time":489000,"text":"It's an Arabic-medium school."},{"time":492000,"text":"She had to translate it into English at her grammar school."},{"time":495000,"text":"And she was the best in the class"},{"time":497000,"text":"at those subjects."},{"time":499000,"text":"Which tells us"},{"time":501000,"text":"that when students come to us from abroad,"},{"time":503000,"text":"we may not be giving them enough credit"},{"time":505000,"text":"for what they know,"},{"time":507000,"text":"and they know it in their own language."},{"time":510000,"text":"When a language dies,"},{"time":512000,"text":"we don't know what we lose with that language."}]},{"cues":[{"time":515000,"text":"This is -- I don't know if you saw it on CNN recently --"},{"time":519000,"text":"they gave the Heroes Award"},{"time":521000,"text":"to a young Kenyan shepherd boy"},{"time":524000,"text":"who couldn't study at night in his village,"},{"time":527000,"text":"like all the village children,"},{"time":529000,"text":"because the kerosene lamp,"},{"time":531000,"text":"it had smoke and it damaged his eyes."},{"time":533000,"text":"And anyway, there was never enough kerosene,"},{"time":536000,"text":"because what does a dollar a day buy for you?"},{"time":539000,"text":"So he invented"},{"time":541000,"text":"a cost-free solar lamp."},{"time":544000,"text":"And now the children in his village"},{"time":546000,"text":"get the same grades at school"},{"time":548000,"text":"as the children who have electricity at home."},{"time":552000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":558000,"text":"When he received his award,"},{"time":560000,"text":"he said these lovely words:"},{"time":562000,"text":"\"The children can lead Africa from what it is today,"},{"time":565000,"text":"a dark continent,"},{"time":567000,"text":"to a light continent.\""},{"time":569000,"text":"A simple idea,"},{"time":571000,"text":"but it could have such far-reaching consequences."}]},{"cues":[{"time":575000,"text":"People who have no light,"},{"time":577000,"text":"whether it's physical or metaphorical,"},{"time":580000,"text":"cannot pass our exams,"},{"time":583000,"text":"and we can never know what they know."},{"time":586000,"text":"Let us not keep them and ourselves"},{"time":589000,"text":"in the dark."},{"time":591000,"text":"Let us celebrate diversity."},{"time":594000,"text":"Mind your language."},{"time":597000,"text":"Use it to spread great ideas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":601000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":608000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":610000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}